  "text": "A significant body of evidence supports the existence of hairpin or lambda vortices in the turbulent boundary layer (see [CITATION_1] for a review, and other papers discussed below). The range of scales of motions, including the LSM and small-scale motions, and much of the statistical behaviour of the turbulent boundary layer, are explained by the existence of a heirarchy of scales of such vortices within the layer.",
